LIMPOPO police have arrested a man linked to the murder of a senior police officer, the attempted murder of another officer and the armed robbery of four security guards in Thohoyandou at the weekend.The 32-year-old man was arrested on Tuesday by members of a special task team, police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said. He was found in possession of a firearm and was expected to appear in the Thohoyandou Magistrate's Court on Thursday.On Sunday Lieutenant-Colonel Phineas Marubini Mamatsiari - who was attached to the Thohoyandou Vehicle Identification and Safeguarding (VIS) unit – was shot dead outside his home in Vuwani by unknown suspects who then robbed him of the state vehicle he was travelling in.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsv6WrxPnho_bgOIcAlk0Wo1aiaLlxMXNysiYmK9dPlgBOZ1-N4XmjZst_LPrGA-SnuVdMQ_cJm5voWOvIjiyrcmX6PlC3TrXdUWHKDQo-aP_eSWTHVs0fSVyZfO7m76-3EtpWo4qDZn0MYRYvlSC8JzDe8tA8wfPtJan95E8xluBBHsSjmEgBVbD4EQbaN4PtoDzd1jID8TISiwRbSSLIeZtniXiSCREqXAiPQkDJacuCQe9DkydbhpibXQ20jw0Vp6EYxDi8SrLE6Y1Tcut0gQWSpUdkg\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzBpGsZN1w6vGEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
